Evraz Highveld Steel and Vanadium Slides to Lowest Since December 2004

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-07-01T13:24:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/evraz-highveld-steel-and-vanadium-slides-to-lowest-since-december-2004.html
Evraz Highveld Steel and Vanadium
Ltd. (EHS)  declined the most in more than three months to the lowest
since Dec. 10, 2004.  The stock slid as much as 26 percent, the steepest intraday
drop since March 17, to 40 rand and was trading at 47.24 rand as
of 3:20 p.m. in Johannesburg. The company is not aware of any
reasons for the fall in its stock and is trying to get more
information, spokeswoman Cathie Lewis said by phone.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  